fragment_downloaded_cb({"url": "gst-plugins-bad-plugins-doc-1.0/glshader.html#page-description", "fragment": "<div id=\"page-description\" data-hotdoc-source=\"glshader\">\n<h1 id=\"glshader1\">glshader</h1><p>OpenGL fragment shader filter</p>\n<h2 id=\"examples\">Examples</h2>\n<pre><code>gst-launch-1.0 videotestsrc ! glupload ! glshader fragment=\"\\\"`cat myshader.frag`\\\"\" ! glimagesink\n</code></pre>\n<p>FBO (Frame Buffer Object) and GLSL (OpenGL Shading Language) are required.\nDepending on the exact OpenGL version chosen and the exact requirements of\nthe OpenGL implementation, a version header may be required.</p>\n<p>The following is a simple OpenGL ES (also usable with OpenGL 3 core contexts)\npassthrough shader with the required inputs.</p>\n<pre><code>#version 100\n#ifdef GL_ES\nprecision mediump float;\n#endif\nvarying vec2 v_texcoord;\nuniform sampler2D tex;\nuniform float time;\nuniform float width;\nuniform float height;\n\nvoid main () {\n  gl_FragColor = texture2D( tex, v_texcoord );\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n</div>\n\n\n"});